### 1) Get access token (client_credentials) for client 1 that belongs to tenant tenant-1 and copy the access_token from the response (or use the saved variable)
POST {{authBaseUrl}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials&client_id={{client_id_1}}&client_secret={{client_secret_1}}



### 1) Get access token (client_credentials) for client 2 that belongs to tenant tenant-2 and copy the access_token from the response (or use the saved variable)
POST {{authBaseUrl}}/connect/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=client_credentials&client_id={{client_id_2}}&client_secret={{client_secret_2}}

### 2) Call Protected API unanuthenticated (no token, should fail) with Status: 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/multi-tenant-api



### 3) Call Call Protected API route (uses the token) authenticated with Status: 200 OK
GET {{baseUrl}}/multi-tenant-api
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token_client1}}

### 3) Call Call Protected API route (uses the token) authenticated with Status: 200 OK
GET {{baseUrl}}/multi-tenant-api
Authorization: Bearer {{access_token_client2}}







